{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"904de03b-a9ed-456f-84a9-203801257f12","content":"Here's what to address in each snippet:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `Form1.cs` — `ContextMenu`/`MenuItem` removed\nThese legacy types are removed in .NET 10. Replace with their modern equivalents:\n\n```csharp\nvar menu = new ContextMenuStrip();\nmenu.Items.Add(new ToolStripMenuItem(\"Open\", null, OnOpen));\n```\n\nThe `OnOpen` handler signature changes from `EventHandler` to same, but the sender is now `ToolStripMenuItem`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `ImageProcessor.cs` — Exception type change\nGDI+ historically threw `OutOfMemoryException` for invalid/corrupt images (a known quirk). .NET 10's updated System.Drawing throws `ArgumentException` instead. Update your catch:\n\n```csharp\ncatch (ArgumentException ex)\n{\n    logger.LogError(ex, \"Invalid image format\");\n}\n```\n\nOr catch both during transition: `catch (Exception ex) when (ex is ArgumentException or OutOfMemoryException)`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `MainWindow.xaml` — Stricter `DynamicResource` resolution\n.NET 10 WPF raises a runtime error for `DynamicResource` referencing an undefined key instead of silently resolving to `null`. Either **define the resource** or add a `FallbackValue`:\n\n```xml\n<TextBlock Text=\"{DynamicResource MissingKey, FallbackValue='(none)'}\" />\n```\n\nThe empty `<Grid.ColumnDefinitions/>` / `<Grid.RowDefinitions/>` are harmless but should be removed as dead markup.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Additional concerns you mentioned\n\n| Feature | Issue | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| **StatusStrip** | Default `RenderMode` changed from `Professional` to `System`, altering appearance | Explicitly set `statusStrip.RenderMode = ToolStripRenderMode.Professional;` to preserve the old look |\n| **TreeView checkboxes** | Checkbox state-toggling on double-click is now suppressed to prevent mismatched check states | Handle `NodeMouseDoubleClick` yourself if you relied on double-click toggling |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3b322ab6